        <h1>Super PAC Funds Spent <span class="red-title">Against</span>  Candidates in the 2012 Election </h1>
        <h4>As of March 5, 2012, <span class='red'>$35,253,552</span> has been spent in opposition, mostly in the form of attack ads against other candidates. This is <span class='red'>54% </span> of all money spent by Super PACs.</h4>
        <h4>Besides fueling a more divisive political climate, Super PAC spending reveals how the US elections are being dominated by the funding of by super rich, making the overall political process less about free speech and more about hate speech.</h4>
       
